					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				Such as, prudence: caution, valor, industriousness.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="left_margin" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						Summus non erit, qui non ex quaq[ue] disciplina decerpit,
						quod ad Scopu[m] suum confert. Id citra labore[m] efficies,
						si nihil attigeris, nisi Locos
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
				<position place="tail" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						Communes. Fortius. )
					</marginalia_text>
					<person name="Joachim Fortius Ringelberg"/> <!--JG: Shouldn't you tag this person above as well, instead of just 'Fortius' (line 76)?-->
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				He who does not gather from this discipline that which would bear him to his goal
				will not attain the highest point. You shall carry out this matter without any work, if you
				arm yourself with nothing but the Common Places. Fortius.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="tail" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						) Locos autem Communes maxim&egrave; 
						probo, qui Locis proprijs inseruiunt maxim&egrave;.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				But I most approve those common places which are most useful for
				their proper places.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="tail" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						( Autargia scopus Autologia[e]. )
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				Self-sufficiency is the goal of self-study.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
